$\underline{\textrm{Explanation}}$:
The distance covered by the car in meters;


- $1\ \ce{km}=1000$ m

The average speed $v_{av}$  of the car;


- $v_{av}=\dfrac{s}{t}=\dfrac{1000\textrm{ m}}{10\textrm{ s}}=100$ m s$^{-1}$

The average output power $P_{av}$ of the engine;


- $P_{av}=Fv_{av} \hspace{2em}$ where  $\hspace{2em}F=800$ N since it is the force of the engine
- $P_{av}=\left(800\right)\left(100\right)=8.0\times{10}^4$ W

Note that this power from the engine does not all contribute to the kinetic energy of the car, as some of it is used to overcome the resistive forces.
